==English==
===Etymology===
[[un-]] + [[clench]]

===Verb===
{{en-infl-reg-sibilant|unclench||}}

# {{transitive}} to open (something) that was [[clench]]ed
#:''The baby stopped crying and '''unclenched''' her fists.''
